Subject: Midwest Memorial weekend campout/show

Mark your calenders now for one of the best Midwest campouts and show.  It
will be located in Lawrence Kansas, the historic town that Quantril burned
in the Civil War.

We will have the campout and show on the Lawrence fair grounds, so camp
sites and camp vehicles can be part of the show without moving them!!

Here are some great reasons to attend:
Dinner provided to campers both Friday and Saturday evening.
Live Band Saturday evening in one of the Air Conditioned buildings.
Camping on grass, with shade.
Rest rooms and showers provided.
2 nights of camping $15, or camping and show $20.
Raffle, Raffle, Raffle.
Swap Meet, bring your stuff to sell to pay for your trip.
Most people are off on Monday, so you'll have an extra travel day.

See more details at:        http://www.mokanvwclub.org/bugblitz.html
